    • Ken01:16:52
      The master branch (main) is the one that is typically the production. You can have other branches like staging, etc. Typically for web sites, the dev ops lead is the only one that can accept changes to the master branch, and then deploy it into production. If you end up working on project A, youll take the current version of master and then make a branch from it, probably called feature/projectA. Then, when you think youre done, youll submit a pull request to the staging branch. Other developers will study the changes, and then try to break it. After rigorous testing, when its ready to go, the lead of the staging branch will take that code, merge it in, and then send another pull request to the master branch.
